### Describe the feature you'd like to request

The following pattern appears throughout the code (starting line 36):

```
$directory: $directory or '@fontsource#{if($isVariable, '-variable', '')}/#{map.get($metadata, id)}/files';
$family: $family or map.get($metadata, family) + if($isVariable, ' Variable', '');
$formats: if(...);
$subsets: if(...);
$weights: if(...);
$styles: if(...);
$axes: if(...);
```

Using if() as a function is deprecated. This triggers warnings and will eventually become an error in future Sass versions.

### Describe the solution you'd like
All if() function calls have been replaced with precomputed variables using @if blocks. This keeps the logic identical while removing deprecation warnings:

```
$variant: '';
@if $isVariable {
  $variant: '-variable';
}
$directory: $directory or "@fontsource#{$variant}/#{map.get($metadata, id)}/files";

$family-suffix: '';
@if $isVariable {
  $family-suffix: ' Variable';
}
$family: $family or map.get($metadata, family) + $family-suffix;

$display: $display or swap;

@if (not $formats or $formats == all) {
  @if $isVariable {
    $formats: woff2;
  } @else {
    $formats: woff2, woff;
  }
} @else {
  $formats: $formats;
}

@if $subsets == all {
  $subsets: map.get($metadata, subsets);
} @else {
  $subsets: $subsets or map.get($metadata, subsets);
}

@if $weights == all {
  $weights: map.get($metadata, weights);
} @else {
  $weights: $weights or map.get($metadata, defaults, weight);
}

@if $styles == all {
  $styles: map.get($metadata, styles);
} @else {
  $styles: $styles or map.get($metadata, defaults, style);
}

$axes-value: null;
@if $axes {
  @if $axes == all {
    $axes-value: full;
  } @else {
    $axes-value: $axes;
  }
} @else if $isVariable {
  @if map.has-key($metadata, axes, wght) {
    $axes-value: wght;
  } @else {
    $axes-value: full;
  }
}
$axes: $axes-value;
```

